CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier , October 18, 1958, pg. A11 reads: "Dr. Gragg Speaks - Dr. Rose S. Gragg (standing in center) is surrounded by other program participants at the afternoon Women's Day program at Bethlehem Baptist Church, McKeesport, last Sunday.  Seated, left to right, are: Mmes. Gladys McNairy, Ellis Blockson, George W.  White, Mary Alexander, Pauline Young, Paul Dippolito, J. Harold Hayes, Walter Lundberg and Sadie Carter.  Standing far right is Mrs. Georgia Pettiford, one of the ushers, and Mrs. Hazel Garland, mistress of ceremonies.  Lower inset shows Mrs. Sadie Carter pinning an orchid on Mrs. Lydia Kidd, the oldest woman of the church.- Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Sadie Carter pinning an orchid on Lydia Kidd during Women's Day program at Bethlehem Baptist Church, McKeesport
